sentences: Daphne Walker (born 1930) is a New Zealand singer popular in the 1950s.
One of her early recordings which proved to be successful was "Haere Mai" that was recorded in 1954 and released on the Tanza label.
She was born on Great Barrier Island.
In 1949 she won a talent quest and was recruited to perform a series of 15-minute live broadcasts on 1YA radio with Bill Wolfgramm on steel guitar and Johnny Bradfield on guitar.
Her first recording was on the Tanza label, "Haere Mai" in 1955.
"Hootchy Kootchy Henry" became a hit in Samoa.
Her last release was in 1966, the album "Coconut Grove".
